---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');
const lastUpdated = '29 April 2026';
---

<BaseLayout title="Terms of Service | St. Claret College of Nursing" activeNav="">

  <section class="relative py-24 bg-navy overflow-hidden">
    <div class="relative max-w-container mx-auto px-8 text-center flex flex-col items-center gap-4">
      <span class="font-work-sans font-semibold text-gold text-sm uppercase tracking-[2.8px]">Legal</span>
      <h1 class="font-newsreader italic text-5xl md:text-6xl text-white leading-tight">Terms of Service</h1>
      <p class="text-[#FBF6E3] text-base">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-light-bg px-8 py-20">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto bg-white rounded-lg shadow-sm p-8 md:p-12 prose prose-slate prose-headings:font-newsreader prose-headings:italic prose-headings:text-navy prose-h2:text-3xl prose-h2:mt-10 prose-h2:mb-4 prose-p:text-text-secondary prose-p:leading-relaxed prose-li:text-text-secondary prose-a:text-navy prose-strong:text-navy max-w-none">

      <p>
        These Terms of Service ("Terms") govern your use of <strong>stclaretcollegeofnursing.com</strong>
        (the "Site"), operated by St. Claret College of Nursing. By accessing or using the Site, you
        agree to these Terms. If you do not agree, please do not use the Site.
      </p>

      <h2>1. Use of the Site</h2>
      <p>You agree to use the Site only for lawful purposes. You must not:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Submit false, misleading, or fraudulent information through any form on the Site.</li>
        <li>Attempt to gain unauthorised access to the Site, its servers, or related systems.</li>
        <li>Use the Site to transmit any virus, malware, or other harmful code.</li>
        <li>Scrape, copy, or republish content from the Site without our written permission.</li>
        <li>Use automated means to flood the Site with traffic or form submissions.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>2. Admissions & Information</h2>
      <p>
        Information about programmes, fees, eligibility, and placements published on the Site is
        provided in good faith for general guidance. Final terms of admission are governed by the
        official admission letter, prospectus, and the policies of the Indian Nursing Council (INC),
        Rajiv Gandhi University of Health Sciences (RGUHS), and the Government of Karnataka.
        We reserve the right to update programme details without prior notice.
      </p>

      <h2>3. Intellectual Property</h2>
      <p>
        All content on the Site — including text, photographs, logos, graphics, and the
        <em>St. Claret College of Nursing</em> name and marks — is the property of the College or
        its licensors and is protected under Indian copyright and trademark law. You may not
        reproduce, distribute, or display any of this content without our prior written consent.
      </p>

      <h2>4. User Submissions</h2>
      <p>
        When you submit information through an inquiry or contact form, you confirm that the
        information is accurate and that you have the right to share it. By submitting, you grant
        us permission to use the information to respond to your request, as detailed in our
        <a href={`${base}/privacy`}>Privacy Policy</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Third-Party Services</h2>
      <p>
        The Site uses third-party services such as Web3Forms (form processing), Google Maps
        (location embed), Instagram, and YouTube. We are not responsible for the content,
        availability, or practices of these third parties.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Disclaimer</h2>
      <p>
        The Site is provided on an "as is" and "as available" basis. We make no warranties,
        express or implied, about the accuracy, reliability, or availability of the content. To
        the maximum extent permitted by law, we disclaim all warranties, including merchantability
        and fitness for a particular purpose.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Limitation of Liability</h2>
      <p>
        To the fullest extent permitted by Indian law, St. Claret College of Nursing and its
        affiliates shall not be liable for any indirect, incidental, special, or consequential
        damages arising out of your use of, or inability to use, the Site.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Changes to These Terms</h2>
      <p>
        We may revise these Terms from time to time. Updates will be reflected by the "Last
        updated" date at the top. Continued use of the Site after any change constitutes
        acceptance of the new Terms.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Governing Law</h2>
      <p>
        These Terms are governed by the laws of India. Any dispute arising out of or in connection
        with these Terms shall be subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts of Bangalore,
        Karnataka.
      </p>

      <h2>10. Contact Us</h2>
      <p>
        St. Claret College of Nursing<br />
        Veeraiah Nagar, Arasinakunte, Dasanapura,<br />
        Karnataka — 562162, India<br />
        Email: <a href="mailto:admission@stclaretcollegeofnursing.com">admission@stclaretcollegeofnursing.com</a><br />
        Phone: <a href="tel:+919847139798">+91 98471 39798</a>
      </p>

    </div>
  </section>

